//! Zig port of SQLite's src/where.c — the WHERE-clause query optimizer/planner.
//!
//! This is the "query optimizer": it generates the VDBE code that loops over
//! tables, selects indices, performs cost-based loop ordering (the "solver"),
//! drives virtual-table xBestIndex, builds automatic indexes and Bloom filters,
//! and emits the loop start/end bytecode.  Entry points sqlite3WhereBegin /
//! sqlite3WhereEnd bracket the per-row WHERE-core code generated by the caller.
//!
//! It shares the whereInt.h internal structs (WhereInfo, WhereLoop, WhereLevel,
//! WherePath, WhereLoopBuilder, WhereScan, WhereTerm, WhereClause, ...) with the
//! still-C wherecode.c / whereexpr.c.  Those structs are accessed via
//! ground-truth offsets using the raw-memory helper idiom shared with
//! whereexpr.zig / expr.zig.
//!
//! CONFIG GATING: SQLITE_DEBUG adds WhereTerm.iTerm and WhereLoop.cId, which
//! shifts the sizeof and field offsets of WhereTerm, WhereClause, WhereOrInfo,
//! WhereInfo, and WhereLoop.  Every such offset is selected at comptime via the
//! off() idiom against c_layout.zig (which has prod & tf blocks).  Debug-only
//! field accesses (iTerm, cId, rStarDelta) are gated on config.sqlite_debug.
//!
//! Config assumptions (true in BOTH the production library and the --dev
//! testfixture): SQLITE_OMIT_VIRTUALTABLE OFF, SQLITE_OMIT_AUTOMATIC_INDEX OFF,
//! SQLITE_ENABLE_STAT4 OFF, SQLITE_ENABLE_STMT_SCANSTATUS OFF, WHERETRACE_ENABLED
//! OFF, SQLITE_ENABLE_COSTMULT OFF, SQLITE_LIKE_DOESNT_MATCH_BLOBS OFF,
//! SQLITE_DISABLE_SKIPAHEAD_DISTINCT OFF, SQLITE_ALLOW_ROWID_IN_VIEW OFF,
//! SQLITE_ENABLE_CURSOR_HINTS OFF, SQLITE_ENABLE_COLUMN_USED_MASK OFF.
//! SQLITE_ENABLE_OFFSET_SQL_FUNC and SQLITE_ENABLE_EXPLAIN_COMMENTS ON.

const std = @import("std");
